						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1245, Rudhirōdgāri, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 5,</hi> probably corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1323 July 9 Saturday</hi> (not verifiable) in the reign of the Hoysaḷa king <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Ballāḷadēvarasa (III).</hi> His <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Aḷiya Mācheya-Daṇṇāyaka</hi> made a gift of land in <hi rend="bold">Maḍuvakūṇṭeyahaḷḷi</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Ṟāmaḍi-nāḍu</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Maliṟaḍi,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Bommiṟaḍi of Būdali</hi> as a <hi rend="italic">koḍagi.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">koḍagi</hi> was handed over to the donee by Bommaṇṇa and Dēvaṇṇa. </p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
